The President has issued an Executive Order to respond to the threat posed by malicious cyber actors. This order authorizes the Secretary of the Treasury, in consultation with the Attorney General and the Secretary of State, to impose sanctions on individuals or entities engaged in malicious cyber-enabled activities that pose a significant threat to national security, foreign policy, or economic health of the United States. The activities include harming critical infrastructure, misappropriating funds or trade secrets, disrupting computer networks, and providing support for these activities. The President intends to use diplomatic engagement, trade policy, and law enforcement to counter this threat.